      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SWEET ON LEXY (8) comes through the Riverina Championships series where he won a heat before racing up to four deep when midfield in the final. Draws wide but he is good enough to win this if things go his way. OAKIE SMOKESHOW (3) added to a string of top-two finishes when coming from wider to be beaten 1.4m last start. Had won two in a row here prior. First try at this distance but he is aided by a good draw. MCBART (7) faces his toughest test yet but is impossible to knock having won all three starts to date, including both outings at this circuit since joining Jason Grimson. Overcame the widest barrier last time and could continue on his winning way. There was merit in the latest performance of GOLDEN TRIBE (5) when he came from the widest barrier for third in his first visit to this circuit. A lower draw helps him.",
